cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about improving the efficiency of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) using a new convolution operation called channel local convolution (CLC). The paper focuses on the application of CLC to image classification tasks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a new CNN model named clcNet, which involves optimizing the computational cost of the network, indicating that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves modifying the channel dependency graph of grouped convolution, which suggests that it may belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method using the ImageNet-1K dataset, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
